description: People are disappearing from the world. People who may not have belonged in the world at all. Secret protocols are being activated. Diana Dane is on a lost highway. Nothing is what it seems.

Author Joe Sacco promises that, in the vein of underground comix like ZAP or Weirdo, "Bumf will go where it needs to go, and do what it needs to do." Though Sacco is world-famous for his serious, journalistic books like Palestine, Safe Area Gorazde, and Footnotes in Gaza, Bumf promises to echo back to his earlier days as a satirist and underground cartoonist. Bumf is a project that Sacco has been working on in between larger projects like Footnotes in Gaza, indulging his love of satire and cartooning. Often puerile, disgusting, and beyond redemption, Sacco apologizes in advance, saying he couldn't help himself. "They expect better things from me. They’ll never put me on a stamp now."
name: Vol. 1: Buggered the Kaiser

description:
Uncle Scrooge takes Donald and the nephews on a perilous trek in search of the fabled seven cities of gold! This is the Scrooge story famous for providing Steven Spielberg and George Lucas with inspiration for parts of Raiders of the Lost Ark. Speaking of gold and movies, James Bond fans might recognize in “The Mysterious Stone Ray” a gimmick that was later used in Goldfinger — Uncle Scrooge’s pores fill with gold dust from his money bin. It makes him ill so he goes on vacation, which turns into a rescue mission for a sailor stranded on an island with some very mysterious baddies. Also, Scrooge decides to run for Treasurer of Duckburg, but it seems the only way to get votes is to spend a lot of money. (Sound familiar?) And you know what Uncle Scrooge thinks of that! Carl Barks delivers another superb collection of clever plot twists, laugh-out-loud comedy, and all-around cartooning brilliance.

Contents

  • The Million-Dollar Pigeon
  • Temper Tampering

Now, fans here can enjoy Spider-Man J's manga-styled adventures, as well - collected for the first time in America and translated for your reading pleasure!

And her old enemy, Captain Steel, hasn't exactly spent the last four decades collecting rust either! All issues, mini series, one-shots including the crossovers with Legend of Isis and 10th Muse are included in this special edition.

Morgan Wulf has been given a second chance at life...as a 17-year-old girl! With the awesome powers of The Muse, she can fearlessly face off against Greek goddesses & mythological monsters. But as Morgan, she must confront the most frightening challenge of all: HIGH SCHOOL!

description: In these stories from HELLBLAZER #84-96, collected here for the first time, Constantine is drawn into a web of time travel and terror when he meets the ghost of Sir Francis Dashwood, founder of the Hellfire Club. Then, Constantine plunges into an arcane landscape where an entity known as the Rainbow Serpent intends to punish man’s treatment of the environment by clearing the earth of all animal life.

The latter, before being killed, would have made a disturbing revelation: Many years ago, him and the comprachicos have been payed to deform the face of a child who happened to be the son of Lord Clancharlie!

deck: Gwynplaine discover his origins. He's the legitimate son of lord Clancharlie, a peer of england, and was sold to the comprachicos following the fall of his father. He wants to get back his rank, he taste what its like and than come back to his real friends... But will he get back in time before the fate hit?

Chapter Three: Pursuit

The Horus make their intentions clear as Victoria and her team of Agents attempt to uncover more information regarding their whereabouts. Riley begins to understand the world he has become a part of.

name: To Your Health

description:
Book Two

Nikolaus McGovern attempts to free his father from prison, it doesn't end well.
name: Book Two

description:
Dayglow Chapter Two

After being awoken from cryogenic sleep, Javier and the Marine Force Recon team quickly realize that things have gone horribly wrong. Instead of being in stasis for three years, as planned, several HUNDRED years have passed. Nature has taken back the earth they once knew, and the team learns, to the horror of all, that creatures once relegated to myth and folklore, are indeed very real. And very deadly.
name: Chapter Two

description:
Lost And Found

Bushi and orphan are joined by a new friend and a shadow from the past appears.
name: Lost And Found

description:
A Mutt in a Rutt

A junkyard dog dreams his day away.
name: A Mutt In A Rutt

description: Joyce was homeschooled, and these first few weeks of college have been her first foray into public education. But now it's Freshman Family Weekend, and her family is back to check up on her. Has college changed Joyce?
name: Your Stupid Overconfidence Is Nostalgic

description: The revolution is underway, and members of hacker group FreeTech have begun to infiltrate the class-restricted upper tier of New York City, a futuristic metropolis sitting atop the rooftops of the original NYC. As they pave the way for the citizens of the original city's slums to rise to the top, Malcolm attempts to ward off an incoming military presence that may be more than the rag-tag band of rebels can handle...

Starlet Lost: Part 02

Niles Lance's search for Zia takes him and Rose out to sea. Meanwhile, we learn more about Zia's visions; hinting at a connection to her past and the horrific Aghori Asylum.
name: Starlet Lost - Pt 2

description: The Flash, Zatanna and Cyborg find themselves in the Mecha Universe, on an Earth that is not their own, in a futuristic version of Metropolis. Just when things can't get any stranger, a giant, serpent-like version of Doomsday threatens to level the city, and the only one who can stop him is...Mecha Superman! Includes a code for a video game content download.

volume.name: Infinite Crisis: Fight For the Multiverse

description: Return to Sanity for the second chapter of stories, featuring twisted young love, a nightmarish court sentence, a Motel of nightmares, arousing criminal activity, crimes against our most bizarre town, and more.
name: Volume 2

description:
Once Upon a Time in Portland

Her soul yanked from her body and sent back in time, things just get even weirder for Althalia Cabrera. Now, all she has to do to get home is prevent an uprising of Earth Elementals from under Portland's sewers. Without help. Without guidance. Without a chance. See what happens when this Bruja has nothing left to lose.
name: Once Upon A Time In Portland

description: Zombies on infinite earths! First, it's monkey on the menu as the original Marvel Zombies invade the dimension of the Marvel Apes! Then, to uncover an antidote to the zombie plague, Machine Man and Howard the Duck set out across the multiverse - battling zombies in the Wild West, Camelot, a future megacity, during a Martian invasion, and on a world suspiciously similar to our own! But back home, undead clones of the Squadron Supreme have overrun Project P.E.G.A.S.U.S., and only a long-dead former Avenger can stop them! And when the Marvel Universe is targeted by a dimension of Nazi zombies, Howard the Duck must assemble a brigade of misfits to beat them back! Collecting MARVEL APES: PRIME EIGHT #1, MARVEL ZOMBIES: EVIL EVOLUTION #1, MARVEL ZOMBIES 5 #1-5, MARVEL ZOMBIES SUPREME #1-5, MARVEL ZOMBIES DESTROY #1-5 and MARVEL ZOMBIES HALLOWEEN #1.
name: Volume 3

description: Captured and facing trial for their war crimes, Onoo and Llamas must put their own differences aside to deal with the common threat facing them all -- an inbound fleet of mercenary pirates! The conclusion to he original story arc.

Bytown Tales

Nick and Lou are still looking for Nick's parents while, at the same time, trying to keep their own lives normal. Not that their own lives really are that ordinary; Nick soon comes to a realization that could send him spiralling out of control and Lou confronts her brother over his concerns about her life choices. Not to be outdone, Moira has a confrontation of her own that leaves her questioning exactly what is going on in her world...and Nick's.
name: Bytown Tales

description: Ah, the great outdoors. Tents, sleeping bags, nature walks, campfires . . . and maybe a few spells thrown in for good measure! In this entry in the series, Salem takes her first camping trip with the Squirrel Girls, but neither Whammy nor Salem is cut out for roughing it. Salem believes a bit of magic will smooth the way . . . but as usual, it creates more problems than it solves. Salem and Whammy are an irresistible duo in a book perfect for the youngest independent readers.
name: Cookie Catastrophe

description:
The gods are watching and some of them are angry. While the Love Punks are in big trouble on Earth, the only people who could save us are seven gravity defying girls from space known as the Satellite Sisters.

The characters are all based on the indigenous Australian kids who collaborated on the story and the digital coloring.
name: Book Two: The Last Crystal

description: "Gasp!" Has somebody figured out that Ward Danforth Woodcock, III and Nightwasp are one and the same? As Ward investigates, he's left to fight a fiendishly-feathered, new super villain alone as Ferret Lad deserts his post in order to score with a superhero groupie.

volume.name: Nightwasp: The Man Who Is Hardly Ever Afraid

description: The teenage members of Pantheon throw an ill-advised party to let off steam and are confronted by the brutal consequences of their new super powers.

Pewfell and his companions have arrived in the fabulous city of Vagus. Tina the Warrior Princess searches for the lost 'Stone of Stone', Kolin sets out to free Gnoma who has been imprisioned by a goblin and Pewfell hits the bars and ends up in the municipal dungeons.

Written and drawn by Rafer Roberts, featuring art by Andrew Cohen and a backup story by Jeff McComsey.

In this issue-

Chapter 37: People's Choice (part 6) - Andrew Cohen takes over art chores as farmers George and Otis visit the hippie commune and dark plans start to take shape.

Chapter 38: Practical Applications of Lysergic Philosophy - The Thixotrope continues teaching Chester about the true nature of the Universe and about the secret knowledge Chester has locked inside of him.

Who The F#$% That Is.

Lost in time, the ladies are hunted by... THE EXALTED FATHER. And if Daddy ain't happy, ain't nobody happy. Cover by Preacher's Glenn Fabry!

description:
Things That Were Once Girls

Private detective Ira Avery's investigation into the disappearance of photojournalist Savannah Loy has uncovered a vile conspiracy among San Hannibal's political elite, but has his search reached a dead end: his own? Find out in the penultimate issue of this neon-noir thriller!

Note: The digital edition (10/15/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

description: A Thanagarian menace returns to Earth, and you won't believe what Diana has to do in her battle with Byth!
name: Attack of the 500 Foot Wonder Woman

description: As the assembled heroes battle for their lives, one enemy’s only ally loses his fight.
name: Chapter Eight

description: Extra! Extra! Read all the Spidey strips by Stan 'The Man' Lee and 'Jazzy' John Romita! The second volume compiling all of Stan and John's AMAZING SPIDER-MAN newspaper strips in chronological order, this titanic tome brings you the classic panels that hit the papers in the late 1970s and early 1980s! All the daily strips are printed in the original black and white, and all the Sundays in color, ready to spin a web of enchantment upon anyone who reads them! Collecting the AMAZING SPIDER-MAN newspaper strips from Jan. 29, 1979, to Jan. 11, 1981.
name: Volume 2

description: From July 1954, "Asteroid Treasure Hunt": A young orphan, Jimmy, is looking for uranium with Dr. Gulliber, only the Dr. is using the boy as a front for claim jumping.
name: Asteroid Treasure Hunt

description: This is it! Volume One of unemployANT concludes here. Will Eddie get a job or will he forever be... unemployANT?

The groundbreaking digital comic returns! Half a million downloads, and the inspiration for everything from Thrillbent itself to comics like Moth City! Read where it all began! Valentine uses the sword to open the gate, but the beautiful woman who saved him is nowhere to be seen. As Valentine dithers, waiting for her, reality itself begins to tear!

Checkmate

Previously in Velica, our hero was just a few feet away from her dad's assassin when she was distracted by Andrew Lounton. Velica chased Domino into his private elevator shaft, but she soon discovered that this was not going to work out in the way that she had hoped. The police thought they had her trapped but she managed to escape by the skin of her teeth. Now, it's time to kick in the next phase of her plan...
name: Checkmate

description:
Spinoff

Spinoff vs. Original

Ai has been bootlegged to a new tape, and is living with the kindly clerk of the Gokuraku Video Shop under the impression that she's a normal girl. But Ai's creator thinks she's defective and is determined to erase her. To make matters worse, Ai's creator has spun off the new video, Video Girl Mai, and she wants Ai off the market!
name: Spinoff

description:
The ultimate WWE crossover! WWE Superstars of today and WWE Legends of the past engage in insane battles across the WWE Universe. From Daniel Bryan to “Stone Cold” Steve Austin, from Hulk Hogan to John Cena, from Undertaker to the Rock. All these Superstars and more are forced into constant combat -- all why trying to figure out how and why they find themselves in constant mayhem across a myriad of bizarre battlefields. But just when they think they know the answers, one superstar changes all the questions: The Hot Rod, “Rowdy” Roddy Piper enters the fray!

When two genetically-engineered teenagers crash-land on a strange planet, they must learn to rely on themselves and their still-developing powers as they face down a giant rock monster. Also in this issue: Lyana the Seeker braves a cursed tomb in search of the fabled Eye of the Sun.

description:
Speak for the Dead

On this All Hallows' Eve, one man will face the reckoning of his atrocity. As Jonathan Dodsman drinks cider and engages in the idle talk of the rich, the wrath of his victim will soon be upon him. A young girl has come for Dodsman's soul.
name: Speak For the Dead

description: The next generation of Ultimates is here! Spider-Man, Black Widow, Kitty Pryde, Bombshell, Cloak and Dagger unite to tackle the vicious, rampant crime wave overtaking Hell's Kitchen! But the young Ultimates are put to the test as they try to survive their first mission: going head-to-head with the city's most ruthless gang, the Serpent Skulls, led by Diamondback! Meanwhile, detective Brigid O'Reilly and her anti-gang unit are on the hunt for a serial mask killer called Scourge! As Jessica Drew adjusts to the mantle of Black Widow, Spider-Man falls for a villainess, and Bombshell's life is changed by tragedy, Crossbones joins the fray! These young heroes have fought Galactus, but can they survive super-powered street gangs and psychopaths? Written by Michel Fiffe, creator of the acclaimed indie series COPRA! Collecting ALL-NEW ULTIMATES #1-6.
name: Volume 1
